# Intentionally does NOT ignore dist/.
#
# compiler/.gitignore lists `dist/` so the built output is not tracked during
# normal development (it is force-added only for git-URL consumption). But
# npm-packlist honors a nested .gitignore even when the root package `files`
# whitelist lists `compiler/dist`, which would silently drop compiler/dist from
# a git-URL / tarball install. A present .npmignore overrides the sibling
# .gitignore for npm only, so `compiler/dist` is packed while git keeps
# ignoring it. Keep this file (even empty) as long as dist is committed for
# git-URL consumers.
